events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen had 29 points and 16 rebounds, Caris LeVert scored 23 points off the bench and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the San Antonio Spurs 117-115 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jarrett Allen has 29 points and 16 rebounds, Cavaliers hold off Spurs 117-115

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons had 38 points and 11 assists, Malcolm Brogdon scored eight of his 18 points during Portland’s nearly flawless overtime, and the Trail Blazers beat the Brooklyn Nets 134-127 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons scores 38, Trail Blazers nearly flawless in overtime to beat the Nets 134-127

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored eight of his 35 points in overtime, Caleb Houstan added a career-high 25 points and the Orlando Magic beat the Atlanta Hawks 117-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero, Houstan lead Magic past Hawks, 117-110 in overtime

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 30 points, making seven 3-pointers, and the New Orleans Pelicans led by 50 points in a 133-100 rout of the Sacramento Kings on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: CJ McCollum scores 30, Pelicans lead by 50 in 133-100 rout of Kings

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving made the tying and go-ahead 3-pointers, finishing with 35 points to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 115-108 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving hits big 3-pointers, scores 35 points to lead the Mavericks over the Timberwolves, 115-108

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray was hitting jumpers. Nikola Jokic was finding open teammates.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 37, Jokic has 16 assists as Nuggets cruise to 131-114 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 28 points and 10 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies, playing without Ja Morant, overcame an 11-point deficit in the fourth quarter to beat the Phoenix Suns 121-115 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies rally with big-4th quarter to beat Suns 121-115 with Morant sidelined

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett took some of the talking points from film study and applied them as he continues to adjust and find his way in a new system.
headlines.shortLinkText: RJ Barrett scores 37 and Steph Curry struggles from the field as Raptors beat the Warriors 133-118

events.name: LA Clippers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 25 points, eight rebounds and seven assists, Taurean Prince hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 1:17 to play and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped a four-game losing streak with a 106-103 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Sunday...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 25 points, Lakers hold off Clippers 106-103 to snap 4-game losing streak
